				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: songs for pulling?<a name="63094"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 20 04 9:13 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My most common pulling song was dispell until I got OoS (still only 64, so no HoS yet). You have to remember that you're a bard though, and you have to be flexible. Change with the situation. For instance, I was in an OoW instanced zone the other night... was pulling with OoS as usual, but the mobs were coming in hard and fast and tearing me up on the way. So I tried pulling with RoT (non-damaging slow). It helped a little, but they were still swinging awfully fast. We figured maybe they were hasted (there was a prelate next to them) so I started pulling with my bigger dispell, and that seemed to help quite a bit. So do what you do best, improvise.</span></td>
