				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: songs for pulling?<a name="63124"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 20 04 11:36 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am fairly new to pulling, but I can say it depends on the territory and the mobs at 65.  For summoning mobs in large outdoor zones it makes a lot of sense to pull with a HoS or other non damage song.  I usually pull with HoS and Rot on the way in.  A 50% pre-slowed mob is nice.
<br />

<br />
In easy LDONs I have often been using the mez and see what comes approach or just Bellow.  If nothing else comes after a mez, break the mez with bellow.  If something comes, you can leave the mob mezed, or fade if too many.
<br />

<br />
HoS is a sweet song.  With various AAs and weapon instruments (1.8 to 2.0 mod) you can easily get over 30 MR debuff.</span></td>
