				<td colspan="2"><span>dispell is never a bad idea IMO.  It can be useful, it is low agro so the MT usually has no problem grabbing agro from you (not that that's a big issue for bards usually, but I used it for that purpose on my pally if not MT) and has a pretty long range.  
<br />

<br />
A debuff is nice too.  
<br />

<br />
Not sure of your level, but the one-minute slow/dot (Anglish Assonance sp? at 60, Requiem of Time later)  is a great thing to hit a mob with on INC (though as noted above, having a dot on the mob can reduce your ability to handle unexpected multiples, and the lvl 60 version has a DOT component).  Pre-slowing a mob especially in tough situations can be very helpful.</span></td>
